The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 4 p.m.  New York  time.  The Merval Index fell 1.4 percent to 3,429.08.    Banco Hipotecario SA  (BHIP AF) fell 5 percent to 2.65
pesos, the most in two weeks. The U.S. Supreme Court rejected an
appeal by Argentina in an effort to unfreeze some assets in a
fund, including shares of the Argentine lender, Reuters reported
yesterday.    Petroleo Brasileiro SA  (APBR AF) rose 3.6 percent to 81.20
pesos, the biggest increase since October 2010. Brazilâ€™s state-
controlled oil company gained in line with crude prices, which
surged to $100 per barrel in New York, on concern that violence
in Libya may disrupt production and spread to other countries in
